{\listtext	\'95	}Freshly grated nutmeg\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs44 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 For the base:\
Pour the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/rye-whiskey/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 rye whiskey}} into a 4-quart container. Fill the now empty rye whiskey bottle with water, pour into an electric kettle, and bring to a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/boil/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 boil}}. Add the sugar and stir until the temperature drops to 190 degrees F. Place the tea bags in the kettle and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/steep/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 steep}} for 3 minutes.\
Add the tea, rum, and Cognac to the whiskey. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/peel/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Peel}} the zest from the lemons, being careful to remove the white pith. Wrap the lemon bodies in {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/plastic-wrap/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 plastic wrap}} and reserve in the refrigerator. Add the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/lemon/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 lemon}} zest to the mixture, and stir to combine. Cover and refrigerate overnight.\
For the punch:\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/strain/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Strain}} the base into a large punch bowl. Juice the reserved lemon bodies and add to the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/punch/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 punch}} bowl. When ready to serve, add the oranges, lemons, sparkling wine, and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/seltzer-water/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 seltzer water}}; stir to combine. Add the ice block and serve with freshly grated {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/nutmeg/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 nutmeg}}.\
